cs.CR, cs.IT, cs.CC, cs.CY, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper proposes a post-quantum digital signature scheme and reviews attacks against it, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper is based on low-density generator matrix codes, which is a topic in information theory.
3. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper derives closed-form estimates of the complexity of attacks on the proposed scheme, which is related to computational complexity.
4. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the performance benchmarks of the proposed scheme, which is related to the impact of computers on society.
5. cs.SE (Software Engineering) - The paper also discusses the implementation of the proposed scheme, which is related to software engineering.
